<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-107-209 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 085 575</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  July 11 1991 v39 n13 p155(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Top-down VHDL design environment accepts graphical and textualinput. (Valid Logic Systems' Logic Workbench TD) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Maliniak, Lisa.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Valid Logic Systems' Logic Workbench TD top-down digital designenvironment can perform mixed behavioral- and structural-levelsimulations of digital systems and application-specific integratedcircuits.andP;  The tools of the system include an interactive VHDLsimulator and a compound-capture tool for graphical-textual entryof designs.andP;  The compound-capture design-entry tool, calledConcept, helps engineers combine graphical and textual designdescriptions in the form of schematics, block diagrams, and VHDL.andO;VHDL Simulator, which is included in the system, fully complieswith the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers' 1076standard.andP;  The system, including Concept, VHDL Simulator, andRapidSim, costs $61,000, and VHDL Simulator, purchased separatelywithout backplane integration, costs $40,500.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Valid Logic Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Logic Workbench TD (Circuit designer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFunctional CapabilitiesTop-Down DesignCircuit DesignText EditorsGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>